snippet: The 6.8-magnitude earthquake off the coast of Fukushima, about 120 miles northeast of Tokyo, set off a minor, eight-inch tsunami and injured at least one person.
abstract: Strong earthquake hits Japan's northern coast near Fukushima Daiichi nuclear plant, which was crippled in 2011 earthquake and tsunami; earthquake sets off minor, eight-inch tsunami and injures at least one person.
lead_paragraph: The 6.8-magnitude earthquake off the coast of Fukushima, about 120 miles northeast of Tokyo, set off a minor, eight-inch tsunami and injured at least one person.
